@* Root component: a button that populates a reactive list, and a root-level @foreach
   with NO wrapping element -- the list reconciles directly into #app (mount()'s target).
   #77's third false positive, closed by decision 89.

   @foreach needs a REACTIVE collection (a never-mutated list is refused: it has no
   version signal for list() to re-run on). So #add mutates it and the click IS the
   measurement -- three <li> reconciled into the mount point, no wrapper element.

   No whitespace between </button> and @foreach, matching If.razor's contract: Razor
   turns SOURCE whitespace between sibling nodes into text nodes, and there is none here. *@

<button id="add" @onclick="Add">add</button>@foreach (string item in items)
{
    <li @key="item" class="row">@item</li>
}

@code {
    List<string> items = new List<string>();

    // Three distinct labels so @key="item" (the string value itself) has stable identities.
    void Add()
    {
        items.Add("alpha");
        items.Add("beta");
        items.Add("gamma");
    }
}
